<|startoftext|>Dish: quick baked roast lamb steaks
Directions: mix the all ingredients except the meat together
shape it into a loaf about the size of a ping pong ball
brush it with the half-and-half
lay the lamb across 1 or 2 slices and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste
pour the marmalade over the meat , sprinkle the other layer of meat and then add a bit more marmite and half-and-half to taste
bake at 350 for 25 minutes or until the meat is very tender and falling from a wooden spoon
do not turn the oven on too high or the meat will become too soft'<|endoftext|>
